      <para>
<parameter>msgInfo</parameter> does NOT specify the new value of the status
flags, only which status flags should be updated.
For example, setting
<parameter>msgInfo</parameter>.<structfield>marked</structfield>
to true indicates that the messages' <structfield>marked</structfield> status
flag will be set to the value specified by
<parameter>doFlip</parameter> and
<parameter>enableDisable</parameter>.</para>

      <para>
Setting <parameter>doFlip</parameter> to <literal>true</literal> "flips"
the selected status flags (each message's flag will be set to false if
the status flag was originally
true, and set to true if the status flag was originalfalse).
If <parameter>doFlip</parameter> is false, then the selected
status flags are set to the value of <parameter>enableDisable</parameter>
<parameter>enableDisable</parameter> is ignored when
Setting <parameter>doFlip</parameter> is true.</para>
